parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Timing Belt Failure due to Nylon Clip Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the nylon clip that holds the timing belt in place can cause the timing belt to loosen and go out of time, leading to engine damage, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: the timing belt loosens and goes out of time

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction for the driver, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioning system fails to cool
the air conditioning system does not work at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to control, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: the transmission is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Paint Peeling and Other Cosmetic Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: While not directly affecting vehicle safety, paint peeling and other cosmetic issues can lead to rust and corrosion, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle over time.
The failure of the power steering system when cold or during initial startup can cause difficulty turning the wheel, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel is stiff or hard to turn when the engine is cold or during initial startup
the steering wheel becomes loose after prolonged effort

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right front tire mount can cause the tire to fall off while driving, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The right front tire becomes loose or falls off while driving
the vehicle pulls to one side
the tire pressure monitoring system (TPMS) warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle sticking can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The throttle pedal sticks or hesitates
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly or maintain a high speed
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe or crossmember can cause the engine and transmission to drop to the ground, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially severe injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: vehicle drifts or swerves into another lane
engine and transmission components visible on the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause loss of vehicle control, making it difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: loud grinding or clunking noise while steering
